[2]
Date: 1 Sep 2003
From: Matias Sacla <msacla@yahoo.com>
Source: Diario Clarin, Buenos Aires, Mon 1 Sep 2003 [translated by Maria
Jacobs, ProMED-ESP] [edited]
<http://old.clarin.com/diario/2003/09/01/e-01704.htm>

No foot and mouth disease in Salta
----------------------------------
"The epidemiological survey produced no evidence that suggests that we are
facing an outbreak of foot and mouth disease." Such was the statement of
SENASA on 31 Aug 2003 regarding the suspicion of an outbreak of the disease
in Salta, Tartagal. In any case, the agency is awaiting the results of the
analysis of the samples obtained.
--
Dr Matias Sacla DVM
